        "username": "GaryM",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/g/b2d939/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-07-22T14:33:00.128Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Thanks for the chatter on this topic, I appreciate all of the responses.</p>\n<p>There is actually a huge need for a type of voice chat using Bluetooth…  I have many biker friends around the world that go on many types of rides. Anything from family vacations to major charity drives. When you are on the open road or in the mountains, doing things like say… making WiFi hot spots on your phone, is just not practical. Data charges would be (or could be) insane. <img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/images/emoji/apple/slight_smile.png?v=12\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>\n<p>I did look at the Briar program, but it was last updated 7 years ago. I am a new Android developer using Android Studio, and the source code doesn’t work well in the latest development. The issues are huge, and I am sure there is a solution to them but it just will not compile correctly, and being new… I have no idea how to fix it.</p>\n<p>Just saying :)</p>\n<p>Gary</p>",
