      {
        "id": 272394,
        "name": "Whatnoww",
        "username": "Whatnoww",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/whatnoww/{size}/54328_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-07-23T08:41:32.355Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"GaryM\" data-post=\"9\" data-topic=\"70566\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/g/b2d939/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> GaryM:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I did look at the Briar program, but it was last updated 7 years ago.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/0/9/0985d6e6b3323c9d915e6b8387212c030e47bfef.png\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"1mf2UtqrzCA8FHqTzM1S0NUTkkv\" width=\"322\" height=\"37\"><br>\nNo?¿ → <a href=\"https://briarproject.org/\">https://briarproject.org/</a></p>\n<aside class=\"onebox allowlistedgeneric\" data-onebox-src=\"https://code.briarproject.org/briar/briar\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n      <img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/1/b/1b9ed5c9db3047a561e2ca4cbcbc8a1623700ed9.png\" class=\"site-icon\" data-dominant-color=\"EE5C28\" width=\"32\" height=\"32\">\n\n      <a href=\"https://code.briarproject.org/briar/briar\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">GitLab</a>\n  </header>\n\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    <img width=\"64\" height=\"64\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/2/c/2c2e41f09d55655ad265203713edc15fc2fa32b6.png\" class=\"thumbnail onebox-avatar\" data-dominant-color=\"90CA1E\">\n\n<h3><a href=\"https://code.briarproject.org/briar/briar\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">briar / briar · GitLab</a></h3>\n\n  <p>Secure messaging, anywhere.</p>\n\n\n  </article>\n\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"clear: both\"></div>\n</aside>\n\n<p>Where are you pulling the code from?</p>\n<p>Bluetooth would not be reliable for your usecase. WiFi Direct would be more suitable and even then, unreliable based on device.</p>\n<p>Honestly the best solution for short range communication are DMR’s, which at least support encryption, but without a license or even with a license depend on jurisdiction. There are license free radios that can be used but are analogue and unencrypted but also short range, you can reduce output strenght and such.</p>\n<p>You’re looking for trouble if you want to use Bluetooth or even WiFi Direct for this. It really is just atrocious. Look at the specification for data transfer, then look at the encoding for an audio stream. Consider that you have to do it both ways, and transcode for multiple streams at a time. It’s not due to lack of consideration that it hasn’t been done. It’s just that it’s a genuinely terrible protocol to try to use for this since bluetooth isn’t meant to coordinate mesh type activities as a protocol. WiFi, maybe more so? But the host device disconnects, and then you have to handle the entire renegotiation and it’s just soooooooooo baaaaaaaaaad.</p>\n<p>I promise you walkies are an infinitely better experience for this.</p>\n<p>ALSO I want to promote Meshtastic or LoRa based network for chat communication that isn’t bluetooth based, but that requires dedicated hardware (as low as 10$ as high as whatever you need) but can go up to 100KM and is encrypted, yet of course nowhere near the complexity of Signal.</p>",
