      {
        "id": 272400,
        "name": "Talya (she/her)",
        "username": "rassilon1963",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/rassilon1963/{size}/31625_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-07-23T14:04:23.920Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"GaryM\" data-post=\"9\" data-topic=\"70566\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/g/b2d939/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> GaryM:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>There is actually a huge need for a type of voice chat using Bluetooth… I have many biker friends around the world that go on many types of rides. Anything from family vacations to major charity drives. When you are on the open road or in the mountains, doing things like say… making WiFi hot spots on your phone, is just not practical. Data charges would be (or could be) insane. <img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/images/emoji/apple/slight_smile.png?v=14\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>how would bluetooth help in this scenario? you’d still need internet to contact anyone outside the car.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote group-top_contributors\" data-username=\"Whatnoww\" data-post=\"11\" data-topic=\"70566\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/whatnoww/48/54328_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Whatnoww:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>ALSO I want to promote Meshtastic or LoRa based network for chat communication that isn’t bluetooth based, but that requires dedicated hardware (as low as 10$ as high as whatever you need) but can go up to 100KM and is encrypted, yet of course nowhere near the complexity of Signal.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>i was just about to suggest that. a friend recently wrote a short guide on how to start with mesh networks, if there’s enough interest i’ll publish it here under <a class=\"hashtag-cooked\" href=\"/c/off-topic/8\" data-type=\"category\" data-slug=\"off-topic\" data-id=\"8\" data-style-type=\"square\"><span class=\"hashtag-icon-placeholder\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-square-full svg-icon svg-node\"><use href=\"#square-full\"></use></svg></span><span>Off Topic</span></a></p>",
